{"timestamp":"2026-03-19T10:09:28.556Z","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","session_id":"0be5f5f9-0c63-4e1a-a140-b68c118374a5","transcript_path":"/home/alexl70/.vscode-server/data/User/workspaceStorage/01bd222c9e9d12cff8e6ef2465541c97/GitHub.copilot-chat/transcripts/0be5f5f9-0c63-4e1a-a140-b68c118374a5.jsonl","tool_name":"memory","tool_input":{"command":"create","path":"/memories/session/plan.md","file_text":"# Plan: Create ToS and Privacy Policy Pages\n\n## Summary\nCreate two static Vue view pages (Terms of Service and Privacy Policy) for the link shortener app, register them as public routes, and add reference links in the sign-in dialog.\n\n**Live domain:** https://s.zlon.info  \n**GitHub repo:** https://github.com/AlexL70/linkshortener  \n**URLs:** `/terms-of-service` and `/privacy-policy`\n\n## Steps\n\n### Phase 1: Create Views\n\n1. Create `frontend/src/views/TermsOfServiceView.vue`\n   - Static content (no script setup needed)\n   - Content: app is in testing mode only; doesn't offer actual services; author/domain owner bears no responsibility for any harm (intentional or unintentional)\n   - Match existing styling: container + padding layout like ProfileView.vue\n\n2. Create `frontend/src/views/PrivacyPolicyView.vue`\n   - Static content (no script setup needed)\n   - Content sections:\n     - Data collected: only email and user ID from third-party auth providers\n     - Data retention: all data removed when user deletes account (can be done any time)\n     - Security: author does everything possible to avoid leaks, but bears no responsibility in event of a breach\n     - Open source: anyone can run their own instance — link to https://github.com/AlexL70/linkshortener\n\n### Phase 2: Register Routes\n\n3. Update `frontend/src/router/index.ts`\n   - Add `/terms-of-service` → `TermsOfServiceView` (no auth required)\n   - Add `/privacy-policy` → `PrivacyPolicyView` (no auth required)\n\n### Phase 3: Sign-In Dialog Update\n\n4. Update `frontend/src/App.vue` — sign-in dialog\n   - Add a small footnote below the provider buttons using RouterLink components:\n     \"By signing in, you agree to our Terms of Service and Privacy Policy\"\n   - Use `text-xs text-muted-foreground` styling consistent with the app's style\n\n## Relevant Files\n- `frontend/src/views/HomeView.vue` — simplest view example (template for static pages)\n- `frontend/src/views/ProfileView.vue` — example of container/padding layout\n- `frontend/src/router/index.ts` — add two new public routes\n- `frontend/src/App.vue` — add links text in the sign-in `<Dialog>`\n\n## Testing\nNo spec files needed — these views have no reactive logic, no API calls, no state. Matches HomeView.vue pattern (which also has no test file).\n\n## Verification\n1. Navigate to `/terms-of-service` and `/privacy-policy` directly in browser — pages render correctly\n2. Unauthenticated access works (no redirect to home)\n3. Authenticated users can also access the pages\n4. Sign-in dialog shows the footnote with working links to both pages\n5. Google OAuth setup accepts: https://s.zlon.info/terms-of-service and https://s.zlon.info/privacy-policy\n\n## Decisions\n- Paths: `/terms-of-service` and `/privacy-policy`\n- Navigation: links only inside the sign-in dialog (no footer)\n- No tests for purely static content views (consistent with HomeView.vue precedent)\n- GitHub repo link: https://github.com/AlexL70/linkshortener\n"},"tool_response":"File created successfully at: /memories/session/plan.md","tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_0166TxFnKxUfnTAkKFWzYzvZ__vscode-1773898184429","cwd":"/home/alexl70/src/pet/linkshortener"}

